    \item Does [Competitor]'s new product pose a material threat to market share?
\end{enumerate}

\subsection*{2.2 Our Contrarian Take}
We believe the consensus view is flawed. Our analysis indicates that [Your high-level counter-argument]. Specifically:
\begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph*)]
    \item \textbf{On Margins:} Yes, due to unrealized pricing power and operational efficiencies detailed in Section 3.1.
    \item \textbf{On Competition:} No, the threat is overstated as the market underestimates [Company]'s brand loyalty and distribution moat (see Section 3.2).
